                                <p>The latest issue of <em>Bike Wales</em> is officially out! This month is a deep dive into historical landscapes and mountain endurance. Here is what's inside:</p>
                                
                                <img style="width: 100%; max-width: 520px; border-radius: 8px; display: block; margin: 0 auto 25px auto;" src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bikewales/shared-assets/main/images/vol-10-iss-44_email-image_01.jpg" alt="collage image">

                                <h3>Features & Projects</h3>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>The Gwent Levels Cycling Project</strong>
                                        Explore the 90-acre Magor Marsh nature reserve and the ancient seawall at Summerleaze—where a surprising find sent chills down my spine.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Misadventures in Llandegfedd</strong>
                                        A planned trip to Trellech turned into a grueling single-day test of endurance that reset my plans for the season.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Regeneration on NCN 881</strong>
                                        A massive 175-photo report documenting the latest improvements along the route from Pontypridd to Maerdy.
                                    </li>
